    public enum FileType

      • asPath

        public java.nio.file.Path asPath(java.nio.file.Path parent,
                                 java.lang.String file)
        Converts a given filename (without the file extension present), combined with a Path reference to a directory, to a new Path reference to a file. If the file did not yet exist, it is created.

        Assumes the parent Path already exists.

        Parameters:
        parent - The parent directory
        file - The filename without a file extension present
        Returns:
        The Path reference to a file
